==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spendthrift
<hw>Spend"thrift`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who spends
money profusely or improvidently; a prodigal; one who lavishes or wastes
his estate. Also used figuratively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A woman who was a generous <qex>spendthrift</qex> of life.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. R. H. Davis.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spendthrift</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spendthrift
<hw>Spend"thrift</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Prodigal; extravagant;
wasteful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spendthrifty</ent>⟦br⟧
